BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:90890b72-94b7-508c-ad7f-3db364d1a113
SUMMARY:Research Grant Program
DESCRIPTION:The Internet Society Foundation’s Research Program supports global resea
 rch collaborations that advance understanding of the Internet and its va
 lue for all. Furthering our 2030 strategic objectives\, the program fost
 ers ideas and innovation that further the long-term goal of a world wher
 e people everywhere enjoy affordable\, reliable\, resilient Internet acc
 ess and a safe\, secure\, and trustworthy online experience.
URL:https://www.isocfoundation.org/grant-programme/research-grant-programme/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260522
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260522
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5a4689ca-9d9b-5aa9-8deb-39855e67c2c3
SUMMARY:European Commission's Digital Networks Act (DNA) Consultation
DESCRIPTION:The European Commission has opened a public consultation on the Digital 
 Networks Act (DNA)—a proposal that could fundamentally reshape how Inter
 net traffic is exchanged in Europe and beyond. We’re calling on the glob
 al Internet Society community to respond\, reaffirming the principles of
  an open\, globally connected Internet and outlining what’s at stake if 
 this proposal is implemented.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/community/news/defending-the-open-internet-in-the-dna-consultation/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260605
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260605
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ec39ebb2-5714-5559-9884-b31d90831ab8
SUMMARY:Regional Working Groups
DESCRIPTION:Our Regional Working Groups are community‑led spaces\, facilitated by a 
 community expert. Internet Society members and staff discuss and collabo
 rate on Internet policy and advocacy connected to four key themes: Safer
  Internet\, Connectivity\, Open Internet\, Internet Governance. These gr
 oups enable you to get directly involved with the issues that matter mos
 t to you. You can also connect with peers across your region\, exchange 
 knowledge\, and contribute to practical outputs such as policy briefs\, 
 consultations\, research\, and community events.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/community/news/join-a-regional-working-group/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261231
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261231
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:11b5c338-048b-5687-9689-cafb49186e33
SUMMARY:Making the Most of the Internet Governance Forum
DESCRIPTION:We're inviting our community to share input on how to make the most of t
 he Internet Governance Forum (IGF) — the UN's primary multistakeholder p
 latform for global Internet policy since 2005. Following the IGF's 20th 
 anniversary and its landmark elevation to a permanent UN forum after the
  WSIS+20 review\, we'd like to hear your thoughts on how the IGF should 
 evolve and grow.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/our-work/internet-governance/making-the-most-of-the-internet-governance-forum/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260511
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260511
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a14cbb63-0929-5f41-b964-2c9b6bc5c1ca
SUMMARY:Moderated Courses- Learning @Internet Society
DESCRIPTION:Moderated courses are offered through the Learning @ Internet Society on
 line platform\,\nsupported by a moderator and a tutor. The moderator ens
 ures all administrative issues are\naddressed\, and the tutor provides t
 he technical expertise and answers all questions related\nto the subject
  matter.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/learning/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260719
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:24837a02-0932-5b8a-885a-a4abdb2aeea9
SUMMARY:Keep Canada Protected - C-22 Letter Writing Campaign
DESCRIPTION:Bill C-22\, An Act respecting lawful access\, would move Canada in the w
 rong direction. If passed\, it would threaten the safety\, livelihoods\,
  and national security of people across the country. The bill would intr
 oduce “lawful access” powers that risk creating backdoors into our priva
 te communications—weaknesses that could be exploited by criminals\, fore
 ign adversaries\, and powerful data-harvesting companies.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/community/news/keep-canada-protected/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260514
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260514
END:VEVENT
